sequenceDiagram
    participant User as Data Scientist
    participant K8sAPI as Kubernetes API<br/>443/TCP HTTPS TLS 1.2+
    participant Webhook as Training Operator Webhook<br/>9443/TCP HTTPS TLS
    participant Operator as Training Operator<br/>Controller
    participant HeadlessSvc as Headless Service<br/>(DNS Discovery)
    participant Master as Master Pod<br/>(RANK=0)
    participant Workers as Worker Pods<br/>(RANK=1..N)

    Note over User,Workers: Flow 1: PyTorchJob Distributed Training Setup

    User->>K8sAPI: kubectl create PyTorchJob<br/>Auth: Bearer Token
    K8sAPI->>Webhook: POST /validate-kubeflow-org-v1-pytorchjob<br/>HTTPS/9443, API server client cert
    Webhook-->>K8sAPI: Admission Response (allow/deny)
    K8sAPI-->>User: PyTorchJob created

    Note over Operator: Reconcile loop triggered

    Operator->>K8sAPI: Watch event: PyTorchJob created<br/>HTTPS/443, ServiceAccount token
    Operator->>K8sAPI: Create headless Service<br/>{job}-{replicaType}-{index}
    K8sAPI-->>Operator: Service created

    Operator->>K8sAPI: Create Master Pod<br/>env: MASTER_ADDR, WORLD_SIZE=N, RANK=0
    K8sAPI-->>Operator: Master Pod created
    K8sAPI->>Master: Pod scheduled

    loop For each worker (RANK 1..N)
        Operator->>K8sAPI: Create Worker Pod<br/>env: MASTER_ADDR={master-svc}, WORLD_SIZE=N, RANK=i
        K8sAPI-->>Operator: Worker Pod created
        K8sAPI->>Workers: Pod scheduled
    end

    Note over Master,Workers: Distributed Training Communication

    Workers->>HeadlessSvc: DNS lookup: {job}-master-0<br/>Resolve Master IP
    HeadlessSvc-->>Workers: Master Pod IP

    Workers->>Master: TCP/23456 c10d rendezvous<br/>No encryption, No auth
    Master-->>Workers: Training coordination

    Note over Operator: Status tracking
    Operator->>K8sAPI: Update PyTorchJob status<br/>(Running → Succeeded/Failed)

    Note over User,Workers: Flow 2: MPIJob Launcher Execution

    participant Launcher as Launcher Pod<br/>(kubectl-delivery init)
    participant MPIWorkers as MPI Worker Pods<br/>(sleeping)

    User->>K8sAPI: kubectl create MPIJob<br/>Auth: Bearer Token

    Operator->>K8sAPI: Watch event: MPIJob created

    Operator->>K8sAPI: Create ConfigMap<br/>(hostfile + kubexec.sh)
    Operator->>K8sAPI: Create ServiceAccount + Role + RoleBinding<br/>(for launcher pod exec)
    Operator->>K8sAPI: Create Worker Pods (sleeping)
    K8sAPI->>MPIWorkers: Worker Pods scheduled (sleeping)

    Operator->>K8sAPI: Create Launcher Pod<br/>(kubectl-delivery init container)
    K8sAPI->>Launcher: Launcher Pod scheduled

    Launcher->>K8sAPI: kubectl exec on workers<br/>HTTPS/443, launcher SA token
    K8sAPI->>MPIWorkers: Execute MPI commands

    Note over Operator: Status tracking
    Operator->>K8sAPI: Update MPIJob status<br/>(Running → Succeeded/Failed)
